pr_title: [Snyk] Security upgrade ubuntu from focal to 20.04
pr_body:
This PR was automatically created by Snyk using the credentials of a real user.


Keeping your Docker base image up-to-date means you‚Äôll benefit from security fixes in the latest version of your chosen image. #### Changes included in this PR - docker/hpgc/Dockerfile We recommend upgrading to `ubuntu:20.04`, as this image has only 12 known vulnerabilities. To do this, merge this pull request, then verify your application still works as expected. pr_title: Config to force stderr in the console (not in a dedicated file)
pr_body:
# Overview
Log the service execution directly on the console (on stderr) an not in a dedicated file for Docker deployments

# Related Issue / Discussion
#65 

# Additional Information

# Contributions and Licensing

(as per https://zoo-project.github.io/docs/contribute/howto.html#licensing)

- [x] I'd like to contribute [feature X|bugfix Y|docs|something else] to ZOO-Project. I confirm that my contributions to ZOO-Project will be compatible with the ZOO-Project license guidelines at the time of contribution.
- [x] I have already previously agreed to the ZOO-Project Contributions and Licensing Guidelines

[{'comment_id': 1493355418, 'comment_body': 'Can you explain why this modification is required?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 17, 15, 19, 20, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gfenoy', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1498945881, 'comment_body': 'Same remark', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 22, 9, 37, 44, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gfenoy', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1498946014, 'comment_body': 'Same remark', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 22, 9, 37, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gfenoy', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1498983710, 'comment_body': 'This change is not linked directly to the support of the logs on the stderr but it is a small bug fix. 
In fact without this change the parameter "servicePath" is not used to define a different path to search for services rather than using the ZOO-Kernel directory.

This change is also mandatory to allow us to move to docker hosting since we have to mount a folder from a volume that stores our python services different than the folder that stores the ZOO-Kernel.

Without this change the lines 2693 to 2705 of the same file are never used.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 22, 10, 3, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sabarre', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1498984434, 'comment_body': 'same answer ;-)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 22, 10, 3, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sabarre', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1498984485, 'comment_body': 'same answer ;-)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 22, 10, 3, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'sabarre', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1500693330, 'comment_body': 'Thanks for the clarification.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2024, 2, 23, 13, 49, 21, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'gfenoy', 'type': 'User'}]
